    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_jc.00329_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <note type="editorial" resp="#ht" place="top">see notes Aug 26 &#38; 31 '88</note>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>MAGAZINE OF ART</name>
                    <!--letterhead includes image-->
                    <name type="place">La Belle Sauvage,</name>
                    <name type="place">Ludgate Hill.</name>
                    <name type="place">London, E.C. <handShift rend="manuscript"/>30 Nov: <handShift
                            rend="printed"/>188<handShift rend="manuscript"/>7<lb/></name>
               <address>
                        <addrLine>To</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Walt Whitman Esq:</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>328 Mickle Street,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Camden,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>New Jersey.</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>U.S.</addrLine>
                       </address>
                 </dateline>
                <salute>Sir,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Having added the Editorship of this Magazine to my duties on the Pall Mall Gazette my
                thoughts at once turned to you, in the hope that you would let me have a poem for
                publication in this very widely circulated serial.</p>
            <p>Will you have the Kindness to <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_jc.00332_large.jpg"
                    type="verso"/>
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_jc.00330_large.jpg" type="recto"/> inform me if you
                have such a poem by you&#8212;not too long&#8212;&#38; unpublished, of
                course&#8212;&#38;, preferably, one which would lend itself to illustration? And
                also on what terms you would let me have such a poem? And, if you <hi
                    rend="underline">haven't</hi> this, if you could write one?</p>
            <p>Awaiting the favor of your reply, &#38; in the hope that your health is in a
                satisfactory condition.<ptr target="loc.03941_n1"/></p>

            <closer><salute>
                    I am, Sir,</salute>
                <salute>Faithfully yours,</salute>
                <signed> M. H. Spielmann, <hi rend="underline">Editor</hi>
                </signed></closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>I send a copy of the magazine herewith for you to judge of.</p>
            </postscript>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc_jc.00331_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
